works.description: Now, this could totally change the way surfers hit the waves. Enter WaveJet, a patented Personal Water Propulsion (PWP) engine designed for use in different personal watercrafts, including surfboards, SUPs, kayaks, kite boards, rescue boards and light boats. We are talking about the WaveJet battery-powered jet surfboard that will add between 6 and 10 knots to your speed in water, which is 2 to 3 times faster than paddling a surfboard. That’s pretty fast. A WaveJet pod adds about 14lbs to a surfboard, which adds to the stability.
